; PaideiaOS IPC Phase-1 Benchmark: MPSC Contention
; P3-018: Contention benchmark for multi-producer single-consumer with global lock
; Design reference: design/ipc/phase1-api.md §2.4, mpsc_lock.pdx

module IpcMpscContention

; Benchmark: Measure throughput degradation under concurrent producer contention

; Constants
BENCH_CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 16      ; Small capacity for steady-state
BENCH_SLOT_SIZE = 256
BENCH_PRODUCER_COUNT = 4         ; Number of concurrent producers
BENCH_ITERATION_COUNT_PER = 2500 ; Iterations per producer (total 10k enqueues)
BENCH_MESSAGE_SIZE = 32

; Workload:
; 1. ipc_create_channel(16, 256)
; 2. Spawn 4 concurrent producer threads
; 3. Each producer loops 2500 times:
;    a. ipc_enqueue(producer_cap, message, 32)
;    b. If FULL, retry (with backoff)
; 4. Simultaneously, consumer thread:
;    a. Continuously ipc_dequeue to drain
; 5. Measure total wall-clock time for all 10k enqueues
; 6. Report throughput: ops/sec, compare to SPSC baseline

; Expected result (Phase 7+ baseline):
; With global spinlock, expect significant throughput drop vs SPSC
; (e.g., ~100-500 ops/sec due to lock contention).
; Phase-2 wait-free replacement should recover to near-SPSC rates.

; STUB: Constants and benchmark outline only
; Runtime: Deferred to paideia-as Phase 7+

end module
